# Standby build-time environment variables.
# Copy to `.env.local` for local overrides (git-ignored), or set these in
# your deploy environment. All are optional — Standby builds and runs with
# none of them set.

# Base path the SPA is served from. Defaults to /standby/ (for GitHub
# Pages at user.github.io/standby/). Self-hosters serving from a domain
# root should set this to /.
# VITE_BASE_PATH=/

# GoatCounter site code for anonymous pageview counting on the PUBLIC
# deploy only. Leave unset for local dev and self-hosted installs — when
# absent, Standby ships zero analytics and makes no network calls. The
# GitHub Pages workflow sets this from the GOATCOUNTER_CODE repo variable.
# See src/lib/analytics.ts for exactly what's collected (anonymous
# pageviews, no cookies, no personal or show data) and the privacy fence.
# VITE_GOATCOUNTER_CODE=yourcode
